title: Information Security Management Policy
summary: ISMS Policy v3.2 — Al-Diwan Contracting W.L.L.
meta: | type: policy | ref: ISMS-POL-2026-003 | theme: legal | date: 2026-06-24

section: 1. Purpose and Scope
text: This policy establishes the framework for information security management across all business units, projects, and third-party engagements of Al-Diwan Contracting W.L.L.

section: 2. Definitions
def: Information Asset | meaning: Any data, software, hardware, or service that supports business operations
def: Confidential Information | meaning: Information classified as Internal, Restricted, or Secret per the classification scheme
def: Security Incident | meaning: Any attempted or successful unauthorized access, use, disclosure, modification, or destruction of information assets

section: 3. Policy Statements
policy: All information assets shall be classified and handled according to their classification level. | owner: CISO | review: 2026-12-24
policy: Access to information systems shall be granted on a least-privilege basis and reviewed quarterly. | owner: IT Director | review: 2026-12-24
policy: All employees shall complete annual information security awareness training. | owner: HR Manager | review: 2026-12-24
policy: Third-party access to company systems requires a signed NDA and technical controls assessment. | owner: Procurement | review: 2026-12-24

section: 4. Controls
control: Access Control (AC-1) | standard: ISO 27001:2022 A.5.15 | implementation: Role-based access control with quarterly review | owner: IT Director | status: implemented
control: Encryption at Rest (CR-1) | standard: ISO 27001:2022 A.8.24 | implementation: AES-256 for all databases and file shares | owner: IT Director | status: implemented
control: Incident Response (IR-1) | standard: ISO 27001:2022 A.5.24 | implementation: 24/7 SOC with 4-hour response SLA | owner: CISO | status: implemented
control: Backup and Recovery (BR-1) | standard: ISO 27001:2022 A.8.13 | implementation: Daily incremental, weekly full, 30-day retention | owner: IT Director | status: implemented

section: 5. Compliance and Audit
audit: Annual ISMS internal audit completed | by: Deloitte Qatar | at: 2026-03-15 | findings: 2 minor, 0 major
audit: Penetration test — external perimeter | by: Mandiant | at: 2026-04-20 | findings: 1 medium, remediated 2026-05-10
audit: Access control review | by: Internal Audit | at: 2026-05-30 | findings: 0

section: 6. References
cite: ISO/IEC 27001:2022 | url: https://www.iso.org/standard/27001
cite: Qatar National Cyber Security Strategy 2024 | url: https://www.ncsc.gov.qa/strategy-2024
cite: NIST Cybersecurity Framework v2.0 | url: https://www.nist.gov/cyberframework

section: 7. Approval
route: sequential
require: ciso
require: ceo
approve: Policy reviewed and approved | by: Faisal Al-Mansouri | role: ciso | at: 2026-06-20
approve: Executive endorsement | by: Fahad Al-Thani | role: ceo | at: 2026-06-24